headline: Realtor.com速 October Rental Report: Rents Fall Again, With More New Units Expected in 2025
summary: Rents fell by -0.8% to $1,720 in October, marking their fifteenth consecutive month of year-over-year declines and falling the most for smaller-sized units, according to the Realtor.com速 October Rental Report released today. Looking ahead, new rental properties coming onto the market are expected to put continued downward pressure on rents next year.
